The number of British women dying from breast cancer has fallen by more than 10 per cent in five years.

The death rate from the disease is now on par or lower than France and Germany, according to Italian and Swiss researchers.

Ten years ago the UK's death rate from the disease was higher than France, Germany, Italy, Poland and Spain.

