However, it's still shy of the European average of 14.9 deaths per 100,000 women.

Spain tops the league, with fewer than 12 per 100,000 in the population predicted to die of the disease.

The findings were published in the 
journal Annals of Oncology after researchers studied cancer rates in 27 
member states of the E.U. using World Health Organisation (WHO) data.

